<h1>What is a relative link?</h1>                                                                                                                

<p class="glossary-intro">A <dfn>relative link</dfn> is a link in HTML that does not specify the full web address because the root domain is assumed relative toÂ where the user is.</p>

<p>For example:</p>

<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>&lt;a href="/glossary/"&gt;SEOniverse glossary&lt;/a&gt;</strong></p>

<p>The server would look for this link in the current directory and as a result would take the user to the glossary page which has the full address https://tommccallumseo.github.io/glossary/.</p>

<p>The alternative to a relative link is an <a href="https://tommccallumseo.github.io/glossary/absolute-link/">absolute link</a>.</p>

